# Fix Gemini Model Typo

The `node` process (PID: 275497) is reporting a capacity error for a non-existent model `gemini-2.5-flash`. Investigation revealed this string is hardcoded in the [GeminiClient](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/src/antigravity_core/gemini_client.py#9-140) initialization.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component Name] Antigravity Core

#### [MODIFY] [gemini_client.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/src/antigravity_core/gemini_client.py)

Update model from `gemini-2.5-flash` to `gemini-1.5-flash` (balanced fallback) or `gemini-2.0-flash-exp`.

**Grandmaster Hybrid Fallback (New)**: 
Implement logic to switch to [MistralClient](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/src/antigravity_core/mistral_client.py#17-149) if Gemini returns a 429 error and all keys are exhausted. This ensures the "Killshot" phase can resume without waiting for the 11-hour Gemini reset.

#### [MODIFY] [gemini_client.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/src/antigravity_core/gemini_client.py)
```diff
-        self.model_name = "gemini-2.5-flash"
+        self.model_name = "gemini-1.5-flash" # More robust baseline
+        # Fallback to Mistral logic in generate_content
```

